BACKGROUND: Major Thalassemia is an autosomal recessive disease with 
complications, mortality and serious pathology. Today, the life expectancy of 
patients with major thalassemia has increased along with therapeutic advances. 
Therefore, they need lifelong care, and caring for them would incur many costs. 
Being aware of the patients' costs can be effective for controlling and managing 
the costs and providing efficient treatments for the care of patients. Hence, 
this study was conducted to estimate the economic burden of the patients with 
major thalassemia.
METHODS: Totally, 198 patients with major thalassemia were randomly selected 
from among the patients with major thalassemia in Tehran, Iran in 2015. The 
